div.head: Prose Edda (Excerpt)
div.p: "A proof of his daring is, that when the asas induced the wolf Fenrer to let himself be bound with the chain Gleipner, he would not believe that they would loose him again until Tyr put his hand in his mouth as a pledge. But when the asas would not loose the Fenrisâˆ’wolf, he bit Tyr's hand off at the place of the wolf's jointWrist.. From that time Tyr is oneâˆ’handed, and he is now called a peacemaker among men."
